FBIS4-31829 "dreeu116_p_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-116 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 POLAND Pawlak Says Steel Strike Opens Market to West Pawlak Says Steel Strike Opens Market to West LD1506203094 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 1900 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506203094 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network Polish BFN [Text] At a news conference in Legnica, Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak has assessed the strike situation in the Polish steelworking industry. He pointed out its international implications. According to the head of the government, Western manufacturers of steel have large surpluses of that raw material. We are losing at our own volition, the prime minister said, because strikes bring our own steelworks to a standstill and foreign competitors can enter our markets.
